rComments: She is a amazing teacher and super caring. She has helped me so thought the semester and gave me such a amazing first year. If you get her you are supper lucking!
She is one of the kindest professor I've ever met, really cares about her students(ask how to pronounce their names), and make sure we understood the new vocabulary/grammar points. 10/10!
Though she sometimes struggles to get the point through, she makes the class very easy to understand and tests include exactly what it's seen in class. Very cute and very kind, 100/10 recommended.
Great teacher

One of my favourite classes and profs throughout my time in university. Professor was kind and fun and never made class boring even though it was pretty early. everything she taught was relevant. super caring and lovely professor, would highly recommend to anybody who wants to learn Japanese!
super friendly pro ! the exams and tests are really what she mentioned in class. the handout is very useful if you wanna prepare for exam.

Kubota sensei is a really good prof. There are a lot of tests in her class, but she always told us exactly what to study and, without fail, everything on the tests was exactly what she said it would be. She explains things really well and she's very funny. Kubota sensei has a lot of energy and it's fantastic. There was never a dull class with her.

Very sweet, very funny, very kind. Make a couple mistakes on an assignment and you'll still get 99%. Course is super easy if you're decent at memorizing, especially if you already know kana going in. 3 hour exam took about half an hour to write even though I only studied the day before. Is very clear about what's on her tests, no surprises.
Really good prof, her class is interesting and not so hard.

She'll be one of the weirdest teachers you'll ever have, but she's adorable and extremely helpful. She goes out of her way to answer your questions and genuinely cares about her students. Plus, she's an easy marker. However,  be prepared to do lots and lots of memorization--you ARE learning a new language after all.
She is extremely kind. The course itself is very easy, but you need to be willing to spend the time to memorize lots of Japanese vocabularies. Don't bother to buy the textbook.

She is a wonderful lady and I'm so glad she was my introduction to the language. She is hilarious and makes sure you understand difficult concepts with memorable actions or even songs. Quizzes almost every week to keep you fresh and the course follows the textbook, so while you don't really need it, you should buy it anyway. Make sure you practice
She is fantastic, and very hilarious. One of the best teacher ever.  Make sure to work hard on your own too, because everything is new information.  She is more than welcome to answer !

She's an amazing teacher, always there for her students and really nice and supportive. Lots of assignments, quizzes, 2 exams and one oral presentation in front of the class. There's a lot of studying so beware. She's clear in her explanations, would take the class again.

Great professor and great class. Definitely will take another class with sensei Kubota. There is an oral presentation to do but sensei is there to help and it is easy to make friends so the presentation is not something to worry about. Sensei is very energetic and wants her students to understand and succeed.
She's nice and exams are okay. Can get Easy A.
She is very animated and funny. She gives very good feedback on homework, and tells funny stories. I miss this class!

Great professor, makes class really interesting. Easy quiz, assignment and exam. You can get an easy A if you pay attention to her, but being absent minded in class is not a big deal because she posts everything on the website.

Overall, great class. She gets everyone to participate in her class. Her review slides are very good, great study guides. Homework, assignments and everything is good. I am glad and lucky to be her student in JPN1902 class. Mami sensei is an easygoing, helpful, funny and friendly professor. I enjoyed learning Japanese in her class.
This professor is amazing!

BEST CLASS! I absolutely loved attending sensei's lectures. She truly cares about her students and even offers extra help. The homework she assigns makes it easier to learn the language. Her review sessions helps solidify learning. I learned so much with her and I would gladly take another class! She's adorable and her slides have cats as examples.
SHE IS SO ADORABLE. She is also very very very funny, helpful, and clear. I recommend her class.
